  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I was examining my wallet in a text editor and noticed that the encryption is listed as AES-128\r\nAES-128-CTR while not exactly broken, is weaker than current recommendations from NIST and would prevent geth from being used in any application that needs certify to current standards.\r\nThe current standard is AES-384 or better.\r\n\r\nIt seems pointless to use the weaker level encryption here and I'm just wondering why not move to something stronger, the impact should be minimal.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.cnss.gov/CNSS/openDoc.cfm?5XLrL7qgAhBGQmbc6LWaIg==\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n",
