    "body": "Here's a good link...\r\nhttp://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/SpecialPublications/NIST.SP.800-175B.pdf\r\nThat one does mention that AES-128 ought to be used for low or moderate impact information.\r\n\r\nHere is a better summary of what you should be looking at if you're protecting highly sensistive information...\r\nhttps://www.iad.gov/iad/programs/iad-initiatives/cnsa-suite.cfm\r\n\r\nThat last link is showing AES-256 so my apologies on that point.",
